      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ETHANS REVENGE (9) progressed off a resuming fourth to lead from a wider barrier and score at his latest appearance at Penrith, getting home by 4.4 metres. Won his lone third-up attempt so should be peaking and draws to enjoy a nice smother. If he gets the gaps he can strike again  HIGHINDELIGHT (8) is a lightly-raced but progressive filly who raced parked but proved too good in a resuming win at Penrith, finishing 2 metres ahead of her rivals. Has to contend with a very wide draw but will be fitter and has upside. LOCHINVAR LEADER (7) showed some good form last time in, highlighted by a win. Draws wide and is first up for five-and-a-half months but has been trialling well. SENTOSAR (6) worked in his resuming fourth at Bathurst and had decent city form prior to the spell. Fitter and is a likely improver.",
